commit.message: Require a sufficiently new Cython to avoid exc_traceback complaints
Add support for Python 3.8
Fix for Python 4
Fix collections.abc imports for Python 3.9
Drop the dot https://twitter.com/pytestdotorg/status/753767547866972160
EOL Python 2.6 no longer available on Travis CI
--use-mirrors has been removed from pip
Remove branch restriction to allow testing feature branches
Fix syntax, sudo not needed and Xenial is default

Fix parsing of "204 No Content" messages.

When parsing a message containing the following content, the
message would never be marked as complete:

`HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\r\n\r\n`
